Package: qsreplace
Version: 0.0.3
Architecture: all
Maintainer: Alienkrishn [Anon4You]
Depends: git, golang
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Homepage: https://github.com/tomnomnom/qsreplace
Description: Accept URLs on stdin, replace all query string values with a user-supplied value
 qsreplace is a command‑line tool that reads a list of URLs from standard input,
 replaces every query parameter value with a string provided by the user, and
 outputs the modified URLs. It is commonly used in penetration testing to
 prepare URLs for fuzzing or injection attacks.
